prompt:
You are a requirements rewriter.
Rewrite each requirement into clean natural language suitable for UML state diagram generation.

Return ONLY valid JSON with this schema:
{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "string",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall ..."
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
1. Keep exactly the same number of requirements and same order.
2. Do not add new meaning.
3. Each rewritten requirement must start with "The system shall".
4. Keep them concise and implementation-neutral.

Input JSON:
{
  "functional_requirements": [
    {
      "requirement": "Allow entrepreneurs to privately approach firms or angel investors with their ideas implemented at different levels for funding and mentorship.",
      "evidence_quote": "Startup meet is a platform for people to privately approach firms or angel investors with their ideas implemented at different levels for funding and mentorship."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Provide profiles for investors and entrepreneurs where they will be describing about what they are looking for.",
      "evidence_quote": "The entrepreneur has to request investors or mentors from different states for submitting his ideas. Once accepted he can send an abstract about it."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Enable entrepreneurs to request investors or mentors from different states for submitting their ideas.",
      "evidence_quote": "The entrepreneur has to request investors or mentors from different states for submitting his ideas."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Allow investors to call for a presentation of an idea if they like it.",
      "evidence_quote": "If the investors like it, they can call for a presentation of it."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Enable mentors to give mentorship.",
      "evidence_quote": "The mentors also can give mentorship."
    },
    {
      "requirement": "Allow users to view and apply government loans and policies through the portal.",
      "evidence_quote": "The government loans and policies can be viewed and also be applied through the portal."
    }
  ]
}

llm_response:
Here is the rewritten JSON with the requirements reformatted according to your rules:

{
  "rewritten_requirements": [
    {
      "source_requirement": "Allow entrepreneurs to privately approach firms or angel investors with their ideas implemented at different levels for funding and mentorship.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall allow entrepreneurs to privately approach firms or angel investors with their ideas implemented at different levels for funding and mentorship."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Provide profiles for investors and entrepreneurs where they will be describing about what they are looking for.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall provide profiles for investors and entrepreneurs where they describe what they are looking for."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Enable entrepreneurs to request investors or mentors from different states for submitting their ideas.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall enable entrepreneurs to request investors or mentors from different states for submitting their ideas."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Allow investors to call for a presentation of an idea if they like it.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall allow investors to call for a presentation of an idea if they like it."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Enable mentors to give mentorship.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall enable mentors to provide mentorship."
    },
    {
      "source_requirement": "Allow users to view and apply government loans and policies through the portal.",
      "rewritten_requirement": "The system shall allow users to view and apply for government loans and policies through the portal."
    }
  ]
}
